cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.CR, cs.DS

The paper discusses the quantitative aspects of computation, which involves the use of physical and mathematical quantities to characterize the behavior and properties of systems. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including logic (cs.LO), programming languages (cs.PL), software engineering (cs.SE), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). However, since the workshop focuses specifically on programming languages and their quantitative aspects, cs.PL is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.LO and cs.SE. Cs.CR and cs.DS are less likely but still possible, as they also deal with quantitative aspects of computation in the context of security and algorithms, respectively.
